The paper proposes a deep learning framework for traffic forecasting using graph convolutional recurrent neural networks. The paper focuses on the application of deep learning in traffic forecasting, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed framework also involves the use of computer vision techniques for visualization, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of spatio-temporal data, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for training the model, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
